<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-07-29T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-07-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="788" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d788">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 894.001 M98/9.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Ambassador of Japan</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Imperial Japanese Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-07-29">
                                    <hi rend="italic">July 29, 1912</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I am profoundly grieved to inform you
                            that I have received a cable message from Viscount Uchida, His Majesty’s
                            Minister for Foreign Affairs, announcing the demise of His Majesty the
                            Emperor at the Imperial Palace at Tokio at 12:43 Tuesday morning, July
                            30th.</p>
                        <p>It is my melancholy duty to request that you will bring this sad
                            intelligence to the knowledge of the President and his Cabinet.</p>
                        <p>Accept [etc.]</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">J. Chinda.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>